1.e4
{ This is called King's Pawn Opening because White starts by moving the
pawn in front of their king two steps. } 1...d6
{ against 1. e4 we do not start with 1...Nf6 because that would allow White
to take more space and hit our knight with 2.e5! . This way, our d-pawn
controls the e5 square and we are ready to continue with ...Nf6 next. } 2.d4
Nf6 3.Nc3 g6 4.Nf3 Bg7
{ Since White played the King's Pawn Opening [1.
e4], our system is called Pirc Defense. } *

