thefianchetto [g7]. From there, it will be eyeing the center. }
4.Nf3
{ After White's fourth move, we are officially facing the classical
variation. In my mind, this means no stress! } 4...Bg7
{ I love this bishop hiding inside the fianchetto. So many opponents forget
about it. } 5.h3
{ It's time to introduce you to the concept ofprophylaxis. As you face more
experienced opponents, they will be familiar with our Bg4 move. If they
don't like it, they could prevent it by moving their pawn to h3 on move #5. }
5...O-O
{ As sophisticated as h3 might look, in my mind it still means no stress.
So, I take a moment to put my king in safety. } 6.Bd3
{ Here we are again facing that Bd3 line, but we cannot play Bg4. What
then? Well, as a hypermodern player, only one question should come to mind.
How do I bother White's central pawns? I want to whistle at them. I want to throw rocks at them. Anything to make them feel the pressure! }
6...Nc6
{ Yes, the same knight attacking the dark squares in the center. This time,
we want to put our e-pawn on e5 as soon as possible; and with our knight on
c6, we are finally ready. } 7.d5
{ I can see the smile on your face! White's center is not what it used to
be. For example, look how powerful our fianchettoed bishop is on the a1-h8
diagonal. However, our c6-knight is attacked. Where should we move it? }
7...Nb4
{ Our knight served its purpose. White's center is now weaker and we go for
their d3-bishop. The main thing to remember in this line is that we play
...Nc6 because we can respond to White's d5 by attacking their d3-bishop. We do not hop into the center because the central dark squares
[d4 and e5] are controlled by their f3-knight. }
8.O-O Nxd3 { Our knight leaves the board with a medal of honor! } 9.Qxd3 c6
{ Our last move should be familiar to you by now. We challenge White's
central pawn with one of our flank pawns. Middlegame plan should also be
easy for you: a] queen wants to go to a5 b] c8-bishop wants to go to d7 c] a8-rook wants to go to the
c-file since our c-pawn will be traded soon d] Pay attention to your hidden fianchetto bishop from g7. }
