1.d4 d6 2.c4 Nf6 3.Nc3 g6 4.Nf3 Bg7 5.g3
{ The starting position of the Fianchetto Variation. } 5...O-O 6.Bg2 Nbd7
{ Once again, we develop our queenside knight to the comfortable d7-square.
Now we are ready to claim our share of the center with our thematic ...e5
break. } 7.O-O e5
{ Mission accomplished! Now White can capture, push or maintain the
