5.Qd2 Qa5 6.O-O-O b5
{ That's it! I just wanted to make you aware of the possibility of White
trying to go from the quiet London System to aggressive opposite-side
castling attack. This is basically the same as starting out with a king's pawn opening @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w
KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@ 1.e4 d6 2.d4 Nf6 3.Nc3 g6 4.Bf4 . } *

