1.b3
{ This move is known as the Nimzowitsch-Larsen Attack. I don't consider it
to be dangerous, but it can get us in positions we are not familiar with.
So, it helps to familiarize ourselves with it. 1.c4 d6 The English opening, which we will also cover in this chapter, is a legendary setup that you
are not likely to encounter at the beginner level. However, as you move up the ladder, you will face it and it's good to at least be familiar with it. It's not that tricky mainly because White typically allows Black to do their opening without any immediate pressure. }
1...g6 *

